Her Edgardo was an Australian tenor Aldo di Toro, now based in Italy.
Resonant and robust of voice, with a strong stage presence, he met the challenge of his two big scenes in Act 3 with honour. David Stephenson’s Enrico had a sinister, cadaverous edge that Fuchs’ could have made more of; the remainder of the cast was on the weak side. The net result was a brisk, forthright Lucia short of Scotch mist, Gothic horror and romantic intensity.
